{
  "Comment": "jpcite credit run orchestrator (2026-05, max-parallel deep manifests). Runs ALL 7 J0X jobs (J01..J07) concurrently in a single Parallel state with MaxConcurrency=7, each submitting to AWS Batch on Fargate Spot using the jpcite-crawl-heavy job definition (16 vCPU / 32 GB) against the deep manifests (2,726 total URLs across 7 jobs). Targets $4-6K/day burn for a 3-5 day full drain of the AWS sponsorship. On any Catch (branch failure / parallel failure / aggregate write failure), emit CloudWatch metric jpcite/credit:CatchInvocations (Count=1, dims=CatchSource+RunId) — alarm jpcite-credit-catch-invocations-alarm fan-outs to SNS so SF no longer depends on email-subscription confirmation. Success-path final notify still uses SNS (cross-region from us-east-1 cost-alerts pipeline). After parallel completion, write run-level aggregate pointer JSON to S3 and emit a final SNS so operator can trigger scripts/aws_credit_ops/aggregate_run_ledger.py for the credit_run_ledger_2026_05.json roll-up. Tagged Project=jpcite CreditRun=2026-05 AutoStop=2026-05-29. [lane:solo]",
  "StartAt": "Parallel_J01_through_J07",
  "TimeoutSeconds": 432000,
  "States": {
    "Parallel_J01_through_J07": {
      "Type": "Parallel",
      "Comment": "Effective MaxConcurrency=7 — all 7 J0X branches run fully concurrently (Parallel state has no concurrency cap, every branch starts together).",
